Rating: 3
Dry roast cumin seeds first and then grind with a mortar & pestle. It adds a depth to the seasoning. I also cooked the black beans in a pressure cooker. They have much better taste than the canned ones - takes about 20 minutes or so. For the slaw, I shredded a carrot and some red cabbage and added mayo and more of the roasted, ground cumin, lemon juice and pepper. I kept this separate and added it with the feta after frying the tacos. Use day-old tortillas (I make my own and when they are too fresh, they don't fold or crisp as up as well) and use tongs to squeeze the folded tacos together while crisping them up in the pan. The Mexican rice suggestion is right on. But a little guacamole never hurts.

