Rating: 4
The 4th fork is for the easiness. the first time I made these, I forgot the feta. It was in the fridge all ready to go too. Dang. I remembered it with the leftovers though.. very easy, very yummy. It totally adapts well too... You could easily just steam the tortillas and have a great meal without the frying. Mix in lime and/or salsa with the beans, whatever. My recipe for rice: saute a chopped onion and a HEAD (yes, really) of garlic, some of it minced, but most of it whole, it will mellow, trust me. Add a chopped pepper for spice if you are so inclined, the flavor is good and the spice will mellow as well. Dump in about 2 cups of white long grain white rice, and brown it for a couple of minutes (stirring). Then dump in 2-1/2 or 3 cups of chicken broth (maybe a half cup more if you like more moist rice), a can of diced tomatoes in juice, and a smaller (8 oz) can of tomato sauce (not paste). Stir, add a cup or two of frozen corn/carrot/green bean/pea mixture, salt a 1/2 to 1 t. or so, bring to a boil, and then reduce the heat, covered at a simmer for 15 minutes or so. SO good.

