Rating: 4
This is the most fantastic recipe ... I used already smashed back beans ... mixed them with cumin and then microwaved them to warm them up ... In the meantime, simply place your corn tortilla in a frying pan with oil ... do not turn it over ... immediately place the bean mixture on one half of the tortilla and fold it over ... I did one at a time and ... flip after browned on one side and brown the other side ... I have these little taco holders ... so after finishing one, I placed it in the taco holder on a warming plate and continued making the rest ... they remained warm and crispy ... then when done, placed the cold slaw per recipe, cheese, per recipe, and salsa per recipe ... I served them with one chicken enchilada ... ohmygosh ... how fantastic ... this is a fab recipe ... however, two tacos with one enchilada is really filling ... so the next time, I will omit the enchilada (for me) ... but for the big eaters ... it is perfectly yummy ... GREAT RECIPE ... I will most definitely make these again and again ...

