Rating: 3
I absolutely had to make these because I love all these ingredients. However, the actual technique needs some refining. Here's how I'm making it next time. Flour tortillas instead of corn; corn tortillas break apart more easily and arent as flexible as flour. The taste you gain from the corn tortillas isn't worth the aggravation of having to "saute" them until they're flexible enough to fold in the pan. The sauteeing threw a lot of unnecessary smoke into the kitchen and it took forever to make them all. I would heat the beans and cumin mixture separately and leave the cabbage/feta mixture to the side. I might even lose the feta and add sour cream and hot sauce here. Assemble them by warming the flour tortillas briefly and filling with warm beans. Top the beans with your "cold" ingredients, wrap and eat; this is how we normally eat "fajitas" and how I will make these next time.

